author: Ethan Strang
title: LaGrange tennis trounces Spalding - LaGrange Daily News | LaGrange Daily News
text:
The LaGrange boy’s and girl’s tennis teams were back in action against Spalding on Tuesday at home. It was all Grangers as both teams won 5-0.
Girls Individual Results:
No. 1 Singles: Dana Song (LG) defeated Olivia Graham (S) 6 – 0, 6 – 4
No. 2 Singles: Anna Claire Lumpkin (LG) defeated Winta Ykaelo (S) 6 – 2, 6 – 1
No. 3 Singles: Yerim Kim (LG) defeated Sara Aldridge (S) 7 – 6, 6 – 3
No. 1 Doubles: Ava Wallace and Elly Sanchez (LG) defeated Caroline Wilson and Anna
Foster (S) 6 – 0, 6 – 3
No. 2 Doubles: Madi Del Angel and Addison Adams (LG) defeated Hayden Stanfield and
Reese Marshall (S) 6 – 1, 6 – 0
Boys Individual Results:
No. 1 Singles: Noah Black (LG) defeated Henry Aldridge (S) 6 – 1, 6 – 3
No. 2 Singles: Brayden Lamb (LG) defeated Walker Blalock (S) 6 – 0, 6 – 0
No. 3 Singles: Scout Mosley (LG) defeated Miles McDowell (S) 6 – 0, 6 – 1
No. 1 Doubles: Jaehan Seol and Sehun Seol (LG) defeated AJ Fulton and Jack Joiner (S) 6 –
0, 6 – 0
No. 2 Doubles: Charlie Battle and Towns Weldon (LG) defeated Anderson Fowler and Niko
Landers (S) 6 – 2, 6 – 1
The boys are enjoying a tremendous season and are one of the top teams in 3A. They improved to 15-1 overall and 7-0 in the region. The girls are also enjoying a strong season and now have a record of 10-6 overall and 6-1 in region play.
